{"type":"step-attempt","step":"scale-tolerance","sessionId":"31eb7ab1-9f7d-45b8-83f1-7fe7764fbe2f","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/scale-tolerance-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/store/journal-integrity.ts","title":"scanJournalIntegrity folds all archived journals on every doctor run","rationale":"Archive count grows monotonically; each call reads and folds every events.jsonl in specrunner/changes/archive/*. Cost is O(archive_count × journal_lines). Mitigated: doctor is a user-invoked maintenance command (not a hot path), the check is required:false, and journal line counts are bounded by pipeline step count per job. design.md acknowledges this as an accepted trade-off.","line":129},{"severity":"low","file":"src/cli/job-show.ts","title":"job show folds the same events.jsonl twice in the happy path","rationale":"inspectJournalDir() and readLineage() each independently read and fold events.jsonl. Doubles the I/O and fold cost per job show call. Not a proportional-to-count concern since job show operates on a single job; constant-factor overhead only.","line":128}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-10T10:49:00.261Z","endedAt":"2026-07-10T10:51:33.601Z"}
{"type":"lineage","step":"scale-tolerance","ts":"2026-07-10T10:51:33.601Z","outputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/scale-tolerance-result-002.md","hash":null}],"inputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/design.md","hash":"sha256:ff300fc7ec1b50a0961fcf28dc4f590e839dca1ace85ed4bc282a283fc566230"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/tasks.md","hash":"sha256:d032ffa876ad68ab8b7f0f67296bb2aa0b7403198f48fef11fca4f7a755e55f1"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/test-cases.md","hash":"sha256:1ba5b736dacb7ef1521a77a709f5bc50c6ad23b237ff739c6160b9d997f6419c","required":false},{"path":".","hash":null}]}
{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"cae2bb04-8e37-4f08-bda2-d96fbe836cef","outcome":{"verdict":"needs-fix","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":false,"findings":[{"severity":"high","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/job-access/load-by-job-id.ts","title":"bare catch{} swallows JOURNAL_CORRUPTED from worktree load path","rationale":"loadStateByJobId step 2a uses a bare catch{} designed to handle 'worktree not found' fallthrough. The diff makes load() throw JOURNAL_CORRUPTED for mid-journal corruption, but this existing catch-all silently swallows it and falls through to canonical lookup. For active worktree jobs (no canonical dir yet), this converts JOURNAL_CORRUPTED to JOB_NOT_FOUND. For jobs with both a worktree and an archive, it silently returns the archive state, masking the corruption. Design D5 explicitly states 'resume/finish/cancel が使う loadStateByJobId も fail-closed になる' — this is violated for the worktree path. Fix: narrow the catch to re-throw SpecRunnerError with code JOURNAL_CORRUPTED.","line":44}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/command/resume.ts","title":"slug-path resume: JOURNAL_CORRUPTED detail hidden behind 'Failed to update state'","rationale":"When resuming by slug, resolveJobStateBySlug uses tolerant list() (correct per D5), then persist() throws JOURNAL_CORRUPTED. The catch at line 218-221 converts it to PrepareError(1, 'Failed to update state') without surfacing the JOURNAL_CORRUPTED hint (git restore instruction). User cannot diagnose the root cause. Not blocking — persist() does prevent any state mutation — but degrades debuggability. Consider identifying JOURNAL_CORRUPTED in the catch block to surface the hint.","line":118},{"severity":"low","file":"src/cli/job-show.ts","title":"printJobState calls fold() twice on the same journal (inspectJournalDir + readLineage)","rationale":"inspectJournalDir folds events.jsonl; if it returns null (clean), readLineage calls fold() again. Two reads and two folds of the same file per job show invocation. Not a correctness issue — both calls see the same file and fold() is pure. Minor inefficiency only.","line":128}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-10T10:49:00.255Z","endedAt":"2026-07-10T10:56:50.279Z"}
{"type":"lineage","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","ts":"2026-07-10T10:56:50.279Z","outputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/cross-boundary-invariants-result-002.md","hash":null}],"inputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/design.md","hash":"sha256:ff300fc7ec1b50a0961fcf28dc4f590e839dca1ace85ed4bc282a283fc566230"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/tasks.md","hash":"sha256:d032ffa876ad68ab8b7f0f67296bb2aa0b7403198f48fef11fca4f7a755e55f1"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/journal-integrity-fail-closed/test-cases.md","hash":"sha256:1ba5b736dacb7ef1521a77a709f5bc50c6ad23b237ff739c6160b9d997f6419c","required":false},{"path":".","hash":null}]}
